dataLineage.statement:
Admin 2 layer was created by dissolving the downloaded Admin 3 layer from the OCHA COD Registry. The Admin 2 layer was updated with new names, p-codes and attribution from a master list provided by the IMO, "New_Mali_admin_pcode_20150330.xlsx". It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following error was found and fixed by ITOS:
1. Created and populated a reference name field 2. ITOS received new attribution from the IMO for Admin3 unit ʺSasalbeʺ. It has changed Admin2 attribution from ʺTenenkouʺ to ʺMoptiʺ. New Admin2 polygons were made to show the new border between ʺTenenkouʺ and ʺMoptiʺ
